description.narrative: Effective and efficient Operations support ensures quality and timely programme delivery, which contributes to Operations Support To Programme Delivery. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The identity, direction and well-being of UNICEF and staff are managed efficiently and effectively to enable the achievement of results for children in the country.

description.narrative: The value of goods and services (including consultants) procured in 2019 worth $14.5 million representing 96% of the supply plan estimate value of $15,000,00.00. Supplies worth $10.9 million were received and 90% ($9.8 million) of these supplies were distributed to counterparts either by being issued from UNICEF controlled warehouses for distribution to beneficiaries or delivered directly from port of entry. The value of the inventory held in warehouses amounted to US$ 1.05 million as of year-end and 99% of the supplies did not exceed 12 months of storage nor were expiring within six months. Goods-in-transit did not exceed 100 days. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
